10:
Now clothe yourself in glory and dignity;
\q array yourself in honor and majesty.
\q

12:
Look at everyone who is proud and bring him low;
\q trample down wicked people where they stand.
\q

13:
Bury them in the earth together;
\q imprison their faces in the hidden place.
\q

15:
Look now at the behemoth, which I made as well as I made you;
\q he eats grass like an ox.
\q

17:
He makes his tail like a cedar;
\q the sinews of his thighs are joined together.
\q

20:
For the hills provide him with food;
\q the beasts of the field play nearby.
\q

22:
The lotus plants cover him with their shade;
\q the willows of the brook are all around him.
\q

23:
See, if a river floods its banks, he does not tremble;
\q he is confident, though the Jordan should surge up to his mouth.
\q
